description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a great time to join our expanding acute hospital team – we are developing innovative ways of supporting our patients remain as independent and safe as possible. We are seeking a flexible Occupational Therapist to bring ideas, enthusiasm and energy to our supportive team . You’ll be assisting us to deliver timely interventions across our acute team and escalation units so delays in patient transition between services and setting are minimalised. You’ll be welcomed into our department that covers the Occupational Therapy provision to an exciting, fast paced acute hospital site. The post involves the assessment and treatment of a largely medical based caseload within our acute team but you’ll have ample opportunity to work creatively and flexibly across other specialities to develop skills and support our service. We’ll need you to support your team of less experienced Occupational Therapists and support staff with supervision, delegation, inspiration and leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll already know the patient benefits of a fast paced, responsive flow through the health and social care system, so you will be keen to work at speed whilst not compromising on quality. You’ll feel at home working as part of a wider team and we expect you’ll demonstrate yourself as a strong role model of a capable professional.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll enjoy the support of a strong Occupational Therapy network across both health and social care in the locality, which brings with it professional development opportunities. We are proud of our varied and interesting in-house training programme which you’ll be part of from the start, you’ll also have access to high quality, regular management and clinical supervision. We’ll offer an excellent induction, ongoing professional support and a highly rewarding job to the successful applicant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our location offers spectacular coastal, mountain and Lakeland scenery, a friendly local community, good transport links as well as accommodation, at cost, if required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ensure that you document evidence of meeting all the essential criteria in the supporting information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If sufficient response is received this post could be closed earlier than the specified closing date, please apply as soon as possible to ensure that your application is considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust is committed to safeguarding adults and children therefore if the post is subject to the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act (ROA) 1974 (Exceptions) Order 1975 (as amended) the successful candidate(s) will be subject to a criminal records check with the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS). The cost of the DBS must be met by the successful candidate(s) through salary deduction. DBS charges are as follows &lt;strong&gt;if applicable to the post:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Standard Check: £26 + Administration cost of £4.20 = deducted at £10.20 from 1st month salary and £10 deducted from salary over following 2 months.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Enhanced Check: £44 + administration cost of £4.20 = £15.20 deducted from 1st month salary and £11 deducted from salary over following 3 months.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of the one of the largest employers in the UK NCIC future employees will have also access to the following benefits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A lease car may be available for this position; further details will be provided upon appointment if applicable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;27 day holiday scheme rising to 33 after 10 years&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible working Scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent opportunities for development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive NHS Pension scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to NHS discounts with retailers and leisure companies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EAP (Employee Assistance Programme) a free, confidential counselling and information service to assist with personal or work-related problems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These schemes are subject to availability&lt;/p&gt;
